{"article_id":"51lZV3rkI9crrzlD","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Republicans warned seven years ago","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that a health care law","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"passed only by Democrats","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"-- with no support from the other party --","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"would struggle to survive .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"The party-line vote","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"to pass Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"they said ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"was arrogant and reckless .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Now , the GOP is in charge ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"and poised to run afoul of its own warnings .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"As Republican lawmakers begin to dismantle President Barack Obama 's landmark health care law ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"awaiting the inauguration of President-elect Donald Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"they face the prospect","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"of overhauling the American health insurance system","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"without any help from across the aisle .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Democrats appear increasingly determined to offer Trump 's party as little help","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"as possible .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"GOP efforts","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to revamp the Affordable Care Act","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"-- some 20 million people are covered through Obamacare","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"while many more have been less directly impacted by the law --","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"are poised to disrupt millions of Americans ' health insurance .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"If repealing and replacing the ACA ultimately becomes a purely partisan Republican exercise ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Obamacare could emerge one of the biggest political liabilities for Trump and his party","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"-- just as it became a problem for Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Republicans sought to paint the Democrats ' passing Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"without GOP support","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"as extreme .","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"Democrats are happy to return the favor .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Making the difficult task","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"of enacting healthcare reform","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"a millstone for Republicans could end up helping Democrats in the 2018 midterm elections","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Former Health and Human Services Secretary Mike Leavitt , a Republican , said","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"an overhaul of Obamacare would only have `` long-term viability ''","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"if the GOP can win support from Democratic lawmakers .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"`` The GOP has indicated publicly","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that they intend not to make the same mistake","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"that the Democrats did","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"in passing a bill","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that was not supported in a bipartisan way , ''","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"Leavitt said .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"`` I think","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"that 's wise . ''","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"But Democratic votes wo n't be easy to get .","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"In a Capitol Hill pep talk Wednesday , Obama urged Democrats not to `` rescue '' Republicans","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"by helping them pass replacement measures ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"according to sources in the room .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"After the meeting , a White House aide said","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Obama used `` Trumpcare '' as an indication","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"he was open to Trump taking credit for improvements .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"That is , of course , if Democrats see any changes","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"they like .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"Sen. Dick Durbin , the second-ranking Democrat in the chamber , told CNN","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that Republicans would be making a serious mistake","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"by moving ahead with reforming Obamacare on a purely partisan basis .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Durbin went as far as to criticize Republicans","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"for refusing to partner with Democrats","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"on making incremental improvements to Obamacare over the years .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"`` We 've had six years of opportunities","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"to work together on a bipartisan basis","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"to improve or change the Affordable Care Act .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"They have never , ever , accepted an invitation for that , ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Durbin said .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` Their approach is :","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"repeal it ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"once you 've repealed it ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"then we 'll think of something new .","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"That 's not a responsible approach . ''","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Not that Obama and Democrats did n't try .","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"After Obama took office in 2009 ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"his administration 's initial efforts","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to win over Republican support for healthcare reform","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"went nowhere","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"as one by one , potential GOP allies turned their backs","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"-- and Republican leaders were happy to paint the law as single party over-reach .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"The healthcare reform bill","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that landed on the president 's desk in March 2010","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"had not received support from a single GOP lawmaker in the House or Senate .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"`` The ACA stands in contrast to just about every other piece of major social welfare legislation in the history of this county ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"which is usually done with bipartisan support , ''","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"said Tevi Troy , deputy secretary of Health and Human Services under President George W. Bush .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"GOP Rep. Phil Roe , a physician","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"who last week introduced a repeal and replace Obamacare bill in the House ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"the law was a `` disaster ''","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"in large part because Democrats passed it","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"without GOP input .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"`` I never understood","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"why healthcare is Republican or Democrat issue .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"I 've never seen a Republican or Democrat heart attack in my life , ''","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Roe said .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"`` There were nine physicians in the Doctors Caucus at that time .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Not one of us was asked one thing about that healthcare bill . ''","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Well before the law was passed ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Republicans have used promises","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"to block then repeal Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"-- a phrase","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"the GOP started using as a pejorative --","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"as a political rallying cry","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"to rev up the party 's base","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"And now that the GOP has the opportunity","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"to dismantle Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"there is no expectation","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that the party will garner any support from Democrats .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"In fact , the vehicle","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"that Republicans are using","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"to roll back major pieces of the law","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"-- a budget resolution","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"followed by a budget reconciliation bill --","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"is a fast-track process","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"that will allow the GOP to avoid a potential Democratic filibuster in the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"when it comes to the second and much more complicated task","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"of overhauling Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"-- replacing what gets repealed --","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"Republicans do n't yet have a plan .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"GOP leaders have so far indicated a preference for the `` repeal and delay '' approach :","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"passing a repeal bill as soon as possible","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"but delaying the repeal measures from going into effect for several years","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"as they develop a measure","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"to replace the law .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"But already , rank-and-file Republicans are expressing reservations","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"about moving too fast on repeal","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"when there is little clarity on replace","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"-- and creating a potential political nightmare","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Department Health and Human Services Secretary Sylvia Mathews Burwell will warn Congress of the dangers of repeal","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"without replace","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"during a speech Monday in Washington .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"The executive freeze","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"The executive freeze 00:51","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"`` If the Affordable Care Act is repealed","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"without a replacement ,","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"the damage to the country 's individual insurance market will begin this spring , ''","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"Burwell will say ,","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"according to excerpts .","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"`` If health insurance companies do n't know","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"what the market will look like going forward ,","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"many will either raise prices","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"or drop out .","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"That means more Americans wo n't be able to afford coverage ,","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"and others wo n't be able to find it at all . ''","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"In a sudden role reversal , Republicans are now labeling Democrats obstructionists","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"when it comes to the healthcare law .","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"`` I think","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"it 's very unfortunate that","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"( Senate Minority Leader )","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"Chuck Schumer has essentially said","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"he 's not interested in cooperating , ''","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"GOP Sen. John Barrasso told CNN in an interview .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"Barrasso and his fellow Republicans","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"-- including the President-elect --","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"are also pressuring Democrats to cooperate .","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"`` It is time","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"for Republicans & Democrats to get together","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"and come up with a healthcare plan","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"that really works","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"- much less expensive & FAR BETTER ! ''","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"Trump tweeted last week .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"... time for Republicans & Democrats to get together","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"and come up with a healthcare plan","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"that really works","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"- much less expensive & FAR BETTER ! -","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"Donald J. Trump","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"January 5 , 2017","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"Democrats vehemently oppose repealing Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"and only a handful of lawmakers","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"-- moderates and those","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"hailing from conservative areas --","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"are likely to show a willingness","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"to discuss replacement efforts with Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"Sen. Joe Manchin of West Virginia , a moderate Democrat , declined to attend Obama 's meeting on Capitol Hill with Democrats last week","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"because he said","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"he opposes any purely partisan conversations about Obamacare .","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"`` I would just caution my friends on the Republican side :","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"the division","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"we 've seen in the country","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"is because we had a bill","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"that was passed in 2009 ...","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"without any bipartisan support","depth":15},{"id":186,"text":"and now it 's about to be repealed","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"without any bipartisan support . ''","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"Manchin told CNN .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"`` You got ta be careful ,","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"throwing the baby out with the bathwater . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":381,"left":0,"right":380,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":380,"left":235,"right":379,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":216,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":201,"right":215,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":201,"left":199,"right":200,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":199,"left":195,"right":198,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":1,"right":194,"relation":"attr